==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persulphide
<hw>Per*sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A sulphide containing more sulphur than some other compound of the
same elements; <as>as, iron pyrites is a <ex>persulphide</ex></as>; --
formerly called <altname>persulphuret</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persulphocyanate</ent>⟦br⟧
